    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "What tools do I need to install?",
        "answer": "Install fd, ripgrep, and fzf using your package manager. On macOS: brew install fd ripgrep fzf"
      },
      {
        "question": "How is fd different from the find command?",
        "answer": "fd is faster, ignores gitignore by default, has better default sorting, and uses intuitive syntax"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can this skill search in gitignored files?",
        "answer": "fd and ripgrep respect gitignore by default. Use --no-ignore flag to include ignored files"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is my data safe with these tools?",
        "answer": "Yes. These tools only read files locally. No data is sent to external servers or stored anywhere"
      },
      {
        "question": "Why are my searches slow?",
        "answer": "Searches are slow when searching too broad a path, not using type filters, or matching complex regex patterns"
      },
      {
        "question": "How does this compare to IDE search?",
        "answer": "These CLI tools are faster for large codebases, work in any terminal, and can be combined into powerful workflows"
